# Resolution 2022-04-11.hom.1: Removal of Chakra Linux as an associated project

This resolution was adopted by the Board of Directors of SPI at their
meeting of [April 11, 2022](/meetings/minutes/2022/2022-04-11/).

WHEREAS

1. Chakra Linux is currently an SPI associated project.

2. The Chakra Linux liaison has notified SPI that Chakra Linux wants to
cease their activities and relation with SPI.

3. Chakra Linux no longer requires or intends to use the services which SPI
provides to associated projects, such as receiving donations, except
with respect to the management of assets currently held by SPI for
Chakra Linux.

THE SPI BOARD RESOLVES THAT

1. Chakra Linux is removed from the list of SPI associated projects.

2. SPI will endeavor in good faith to transfer all assets currently held by
SPI for Chakra Linux to the SPI General fund within a reasonable time
from the date of approval of this resolution.

3. SPI will no longer actively seek donations on behalf of Chakra Linux.

4. This is subject to any undischarged obligations SPI may have with
respect to Chakra Linux. We are not aware of any such undischarged
obligations. We ask anyone who is aware of any to notify us within 30
days of this resolution.
